parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes do not respond or engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle does not stop or slow down
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle goes into a skid
the transmission locks up
the rear brakes do not work
the front brakes wear out quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brakes do not work
the front brakes do all the braking
the front brakes wear out quickly
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle goes into a skid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden collapse of the seat backrest can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The driver's seat backrest collapses rearward while driving
the seat backrest falls backward when entering or exiting the vehicle
the seat backrest does not return to its upright position
the seat backrest collapses when leaned against
the bolts in the seat mechanism shear off
the seat falls backward while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to extend out of the holster
the seat belt is worn and frayed
the seat belt jams inside the retractor assembly
the seat belt does not restrain the driver or passenger during an accident.
